content.description: Start way low and left down in the largest part of the ceilings matched on an undercling. Do a V7 crux right off the bat, then follow the obvious features up and right to another V7 mid way. Finish matched on the last jug before the roof completely blanks out.
content.location: In the largest part of the ceilings, on the left side. The most obvious line of weakness through an otherwise blank roof.

content.description: Sit start in the middle of the boulder matched in a slanted rail. Climb slightly up and left to the most amazing horn jug, then climb up and right to a tricky topout.
content.location: If looking at the ceilings, make your way to the downhill side of the boulders. Moe is a stand alone boulder that can't be missed.

content.description: Stand start on obvious huge triangular shaped jug. Climb straight up through the large dihedral on jugs and cracks. Dropoff from the jug halfway up the slab, or topout bush-wack style.
content.location: Dead center in the right section of the Ceilings, in between No Ceilings and The Dojo. Obvious dihedral with good holds.

content.description: The right most climb in the Ceilings, start on a juggy seam. Move through decent holds on the roof to a crazy lip encounter using the only real hold- a bad sloper. Drop off after you've gained the slab, or cruise the V1ish highball to the top.
content.location: Right most line in the ceilings.

content.description: The End Zone is the continuation of the cliffline as it rounds the point. A series of large roofs dubbed "the ceilings" face uphill, along with a laberynth of easier climbs.There are half a dozen futuristic double-digit projects in this sector.
